<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="477" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d477">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.1211/65: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico
                                        City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-04-21T22:00:00-07:00"><hi rend="italic">April 21,
                                        1923—10 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received April 22—1:02
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>25. Your 31 April 20, 6 p.m. Identic statement proposed by Mr. Pani
                            transmitted textually in my cipher telegram 24 April 19, 6 p.m. will be
                            published here in the newspapers Tuesday morning April 24th. If date is
                            satisfactory to the Department please instruct.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>